structure.name: UBX-UPD-SOS
structure.description: Backup and restore functions for battery-backed memory (BBR) in flash memory, including polling status, creating/clearing backups, and receiving acknowledgements/status updates.

fields.name: cmd
fields.description: Command or status identifier. (Present in 4-byte and 8-byte variants)

bits.name: Create backup
bits.description: Input command: Save part of the battery-backed memory (BBR) in flash.

bits.name: Clear backup
bits.description: Input command: Erase the backup file present in flash.

bits.name: Backup creation acknowledge
bits.description: Output message: Confirmation of creation of a backup file in flash.

bits.name: System restored from backup
bits.description: Output message: Notification that the BBR has been restored from a backup file in flash.

fields.name: reserved0
fields.description: Reserved

fields.name: response
fields.description: Response status (only present in 8-byte output messages, i.e., when cmd is 2 or 3).

bits.name: Not acknowledged
bits.description: Response for cmd=2: Backup not acknowledged.

bits.name: Failed restoring from backup
bits.description: Response for cmd=3: Failed restoring from backup.

bits.name: Restored from backup
bits.description: Response for cmd=3: System restored from backup.

bits.name: Not restored (no backup)
bits.description: Response for cmd=3: System not restored (no backup).

fields.name: reserved1
fields.description: Reserved

structure.name: UBX-UPD-SOS
structure.description: The UBX-UPD-SOS message is used for managing backup and restore operations for flash memory, encompassing poll requests, input commands, and output acknowledgements/notifications.

fields.name: cmd
fields.description:
Command identifier / Message type. This field is present when the payload length is 4 or 8 bytes. Its value determines the message variant:
0 = Create backup command (Input)
1 = Clear backup command (Input)
2 = Backup creation acknowledge (Output)
3 = System restored from backup notification (Output)

fields.name: reserved0
fields.description: Reserved bytes. Present when the payload length is 4 or 8 bytes.

fields.name: response
fields.description:
Response status. This field is present when cmd is 2 or 3 (payload length 8 bytes).
If cmd = 2: 0 = Not acknowledged, 1 = Acknowledged.
If cmd = 3: 0 = Unknown, 1 = Failed restoring from backup, 2 = Restored from backup, 3 = Not restored (no backup).

fields.name: reserved1
fields.description: Reserved bytes. Present when cmd is 2 or 3 (payload length 8 bytes).

structure.name: UBX-UPD-SOS
structure.description: Message for backup and restore operations of the battery-backed memory (BBR) in flash, supporting polling, creation, clearing, and status reporting.

fields.name: cmd
fields.description:
Command / Status type. Determines payload interpretation and length. When length is 0, this field is not present (Poll request). When present:
0 = Create backup (Input)
1 = Clear backup (Input)
2 = Poll backup restore status (Input, expecting an 8-byte response payload)
3 = System restored from backup (Output, 8-byte payload)

fields.name: reserved0
fields.description: Reserved. Present in 4-byte and 8-byte payloads.

fields.name: response
fields.description:
Response status. Only present for 8-byte payloads (when cmd is 2 or 3).
If cmd = 2 (Poll backup restore status - Input):
0 = Not acknowledged
1 = Acknowledged
If cmd = 3 (System restored from backup - Output):
0 = Unknown
1 = Failed restoring from backup
2 = Restored from backup
3 = Not restored (no backup)

fields.name: reserved1
fields.description: Reserved. Present in 8-byte payloads.

structure.name: UBX-UPD-SOS
structure.description: Messages in the UBX-UPD-SOS class are used for firmware backup management. This message identifier (0x09 0x14) is used for multiple purposes: a 0-byte payload for polling backup restore status; 4-byte payloads for 'Create backup in flash' (cmd=0) or 'Clear backup in flash' (cmd=1) commands; and 8-byte payloads for 'Backup creation acknowledge' (cmd=2) or 'System restored from backup' (cmd=3) outputs. The fields below describe the 8-byte output message format, which is the most comprehensive payload for this message ID.

fields.name: cmd
fields.description:
Command or status indicator:
- 0: Used for 'Create backup in flash' (input command)
- 1: Used for 'Clear backup in flash' (input command)
- 2: Used for 'Backup creation acknowledge' (output)
- 3: Used for 'System restored from backup' (output)

fields.name: reserved0
fields.description: Reserved

fields.name: response
fields.description:
Response status (relevant when 'cmd' is 2 or 3):
- When cmd=2 (Backup creation acknowledge):
  - 0: Not acknowledged
  - 1: Acknowledged
- When cmd=3 (System restored from backup):
  - 0: Unknown
  - 1: Failed restoring from backup
  - 2: Restored from backup
  - 3: Not restored (no backup)

fields.name: reserved1
fields.description: Reserved

structure.name: UBX-UPD-SOS
structure.description: Backup/restore status and commands for battery-backed memory, handling poll requests, create/clear commands, and acknowledge/system restored outputs.

variable.formula: Payload length can be 0 (poll request), 4 (create/clear commands), or 8 (acknowledge/restored outputs) depending on the message purpose.

fields.name: cmd
fields.description:
Command. Defines the message purpose. Present for 4-byte and 8-byte payloads. Not present for 0-byte poll requests.
0 = Create backup in flash
1 = Clear backup in flash
2 = Backup creation acknowledge
3 = System restored from backup

fields.name: reserved0
fields.description: Reserved. Present for 4-byte and 8-byte payloads. Not present for 0-byte poll requests.

fields.name: response
fields.description:
Response status. Present only for 8-byte payloads (cmd=2 or cmd=3). 
If cmd=2 (Backup creation acknowledge): 0=Not acknowledged, 1=Acknowledged.
If cmd=3 (System restored from backup): 0=Unknown, 1=Failed restoring from backup, 2=Restored from backup, 3=Not restored (no backup).

fields.name: reserved1
fields.description: Reserved. Present only for 8-byte payloads (cmd=2 or cmd=3).
